Senate Judiciary 1
Amendment No. 1 to SB1984
Gardenhire
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1984* House Bill No. 1933
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1.
(a) The Tennessee advisory commission on intergovernmental relations (TACIR)
shall study and prepare a report on:
(1) Pay equity for assistant district attorneys general in this state; and
(2) The caseloads of assistant district attorneys general in each judicial
district, including:
(A) The number of cases indicted or charged;
(B) The number of cases that go to trial;
(C) The number of cases that result in a conviction and
suspended sentence, probation, or diversion; and
(D) A comparison of the caseloads, including the measures in
subdivisions (a)(2)(A)-(C), for assistant district attorneys general in
judicial districts of similar populations.
(b) All appropriate state departments and agencies shall provide assistance to
TACIR in connection with the study. On or before January 31, 2027, TACIR shall report
SA0904
